message.content:
Today's Healthy Meal Plan:

Breakfast:
- Greek Yogurt with mixed berries and chia seeds: Blend 1 cup of Greek yogurt with 1/4 cup of mixed berries (fresh or frozen) and 1 tablespoon of chia seeds. Mix well and enjoy!

Morning Snack:
- Apple and Cottage Cheese Salad: Peel and thinly slice an apple, then toss with 1/2 cup of cottage cheese and a sprinkle of oats for texture. Drizzle with your favorite balsamic vinaigrette.

Lunch:
- Chickpea Salad: Combine 1 can of chickpeas (drained and rinsed) with 1/4 cup of cherry tomatoes, 1/2 avocado, 1/4 cup of red onion, and a sprinkle of parsley. Dress with your favorite balsamic vinaigrette.

Afternoon Snack:
- Protein Power Bar: Make a simple protein power bar by combining 3 tablespoons of almond butter with 1/4 cup of mixed berries (fresh or frozen) and a sprinkle of chia seeds. Mix well and enjoy!

Dinner:
- Baked Salmon with Quinoa: Prepare 4 salmon fillets by coating them in lemon juice, seasoning with salt and pepper, and baking at 375°F for 10 minutes on each side. Serve over a bed of cooked quinoa and steamed broccoli.

Evening Snack:
- Carrot Zucchini Sushi: Peel and thinly slice 2 carrots and 2 zucchini lengthwise, then roll them up with a little avocado for dipping. Serve with your favorite sriracha sauce.
